Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Pour the boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @egg noodle nests{2} and cook until tender, ~{4%mins}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British pork mince{240%g} and sprinkle over the @Indonesian style spice mix{1}.

Fry the mince until browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the pork cooks, halve the @bell pepper{1} and remove the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onions{2}.

Crush the @salted peanuts{25} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}. Halve the @lime{1/2}.

Once the mince is cooked, drain and discard any excess fat. Add the pepper and cook until softened, ~{3-4%mins}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix the @ketjap manis{50%ml} with the @rice vinegar{15%ml}, @honey{15%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce. Squeeze in the lime juice, then combine well.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Add the spring onions and sauce mixture to your stir-fry, then bring to the boil.

Bubble until thickened and glossy, ~{2-3%mins}.

When the sauce has thickened, add the cooked noodles and half the peanuts.

Stir to coat the noodles in the sauce and cook until everything's piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste and season with @salt and @pepper if needed.

Share the pork noodles between your #bowls{}.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining peanuts for those who'd like them. Enjoy!